field.value:
The getter of OutputStream property in MockResponse always returns a new instance of MemoryStream which prevents from testing an action such as:

public void Render() {
    byte[] buffer = pdfService.ConstructPdf();
    Response.OutputStream.Write(buffer, 0, buffer.Length);
    Response.ContentType = "application/pdf";
    CancelView();
}

There is no way to verify that something has been written to the OutputStream.
